## How to add a new API route

{{#isHono}}
In `apps/api/src/index.ts`:
```ts
app.get('/api/your-route', async (c) => {
  return c.json({ data: 'your response' });
});
```
{{/isHono}}
{{#isFastapi}}
In `apps/api/main.py`:
```python
@app.get("/api/your-route")
def your_route():
    return {"data": "your response"}
```
{{/isFastapi}}
{{#isGo}}
In `apps/api/cmd/api/main.go`, add to `main()`:
```go
mux.HandleFunc("GET /api/your-route", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    writeJSON(w, http.StatusOK, map[string]string{"data": "your response"})
})
```
{{/isGo}}

{{#isReactVite}}
The frontend proxies `/api/*` to `http://localhost:8080` via `vite.config.ts`. So `fetch('/api/your-route')` works in development without CORS issues.
{{/isReactVite}}

