## How `npm run deploy` works

1. Reads `vibe.config.json` to determine deployment targets
2. Runs `npm run build:web` (if frontend exists)
3. Deploys frontend to {{#isCloudflarePages}}Cloudflare Pages via `wrangler`{{/isCloudflarePages}}{{#isVercel}}Vercel via `vercel --prod`{{/isVercel}}{{#isFirebaseHosting}}Firebase via `firebase deploy`{{/isFirebaseHosting}}{{#isNetlify}}Netlify via `netlify-cli`{{/isNetlify}}
{{#hasApi}}4. Deploys backend to {{#isCloudRun}}Cloud Run via `gcloud run deploy`{{/isCloudRun}}{{#isRender}}Render (auto via git push){{/isRender}}{{#isFlyio}}Fly.io via `flyctl deploy`{{/isFlyio}}{{/hasApi}}

For CI/CD, GitHub Actions runs the same steps automatically on push to `main` using stored secrets.

