## Common mistakes to avoid

{{#isReactVite}}
- Don't add `.env` variables without the `VITE_` prefix if you need them in the browser — Vite only exposes `VITE_*` vars to the client bundle
{{/isReactVite}}
{{#isNextjs}}
- Server components can't use hooks or browser APIs — add `'use client'` directive when needed
- Don't import server-only code in client components
{{/isNextjs}}
{{#hasClerk}}
- Never expose `CLERK_SECRET_KEY` to the browser — it's server-side only
{{/hasClerk}}
{{#hasStripe}}
- Never expose `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` to the browser — use the publishable key on the client
- Always verify webhook signatures before processing events
{{/hasStripe}}
{{#hasNeon}}
- Don't create a new `neon()` connection on every request — initialize it once at module level
{{/hasNeon}}
{{#isCloudRun}}
- Cloud Run sets the `PORT` env var — always use `process.env.PORT ?? 8080`, never hardcode the port
- The container must start and be ready within 240 seconds or Cloud Run marks the deployment as failed
{{/isCloudRun}}
